{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["SPACECRAFT INSTRUMENTATION"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "created": "2013-08-12T10:06:00.0000000+00:00", "distributionDate": "2011-08-18T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "The benefits of satellite-based radar altimetry for oceanographic research are discussed in connection with the Seasat Altimeter Data Seminar. After a general review of the oceanographic data collected by the Seasat and GEOS-3 satellites, a number of criteria are proposed for the successful operation of a satellite-based radar altimeter for oceanographic remote sensing applications. It is shown how the interpretation of altimeter return power waveforms can be used to calculate wind speed, ocean circulation and variability in wind, waves, and tides. A number of recommendations for improving the accuracy of radar altimeter data are given which may be incorporated in the design of the GEOSAT and TOPEX research satellites.", "title": "The potential of satellite-based radar altimeters", "stiType": "REPRINT", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-12T10:06:00.0000000+00:00", "isLessonsLearned": false, "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19850030646, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Mooers, C. N. K."}, "organization": {"name": "U.S. Naval Postgraduate School", "location": "Monterey, CA, United States"}}, "id": "b95825b8346146ae9d6c7f96b8a34093"}, {"sequence": 1, "submissionId": 19850030646, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Barrick, D. E."}, "organization": {"name": "Ocean Surface Research, Inc.", "location": "Boulder, CO, United States"}}, "id": "303d99ec46c349dba09eb9b1f1cebe57"}, {"sequence": 2, "submissionId": 19850030646, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Cheney, R. 